definition.value: An L-alpha-amino acid residue in which HOEtN is conjugated to the epsilon position of an L-lysine residue.

An L-alpha-amino acid residue in which 3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonic acid (Kdo) is conjugated to the epsilon position of an L-lysine residue via adipic acid dihydrazide (ADH) and adipic acid bis(N-hydroxysuccinimide) (SIDEA) linkers.
A member of the class of ureas that is N-carbamoylglycine in which the pro-R hydrogen has been replaced by a phenyl group.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue in which adipic acid dihydrazide (ADH) is conjugated to the epsilon position of an L-lysine residue via an adipic acid bis(N-hydroxysuccinimide) (SIDEA) linker.
An L-alpha-amino acid residue in which an adipic acid bis(N-hydroxysuccinimide) (SIDEA) linker is conjugated to the epsilon position of the L-lysine residue.
